This paper deals with algorithms for sampling 3-orientations of planar triangulations, which is a problem in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also discusses Markov chains and their mixing rates, which are topics in computer science theory (cs.DS) and graph theory (cs.GT). Finally, the paper mentions applications of the sampling algorithms to other combinatorial structures, which could fall under the category of computational combinatorics (cs.SI).
